Then your English must be good.

470
00:40:35,150 --> 00:40:37,338
Are you a native speaker? Please teach me.

471
00:40:37,421 --> 00:40:39,526
Should we start a TOEIC study group?

472
00:40:41,422 --> 00:40:43,145
No, I'm not good at it.

473
00:40:43,780 --> 00:40:45,184
What major are you again?

474
00:40:46,230 --> 00:40:47,074
Aesthetics.

475
00:40:47,157 --> 00:40:50,433
I used to paint, but I haven't been
able to after coming to Korea.

476
00:40:51,350 --> 00:40:54,427
- You paint but are in Aesthetics?
- I know, right?

477
00:40:54,510 --> 00:40:55,409
Yu-mi.

478
00:40:58,117 --> 00:40:58,962
Small.

479
00:40:59,045 --> 00:41:01,200
- It's perfect.
- It suits you.

480
00:41:01,283 --> 00:41:03,342
You can have it. It's free for freshmen.

481
00:41:03,425 --> 00:41:06,523
EHYEON WOMANS UNIVERSITY MAGAZINE

482
00:41:15,805 --> 00:41:18,568
AESTHETICS ODYSSEY

483
00:41:18,651 --> 00:41:20,622
Yu-mi, did you read this?

484
00:41:20,705 --> 00:41:21,774
WHO MOVED MY CHEESE?

485
00:41:21,857 --> 00:41:23,330
No? Do you want to borrow it?

486
00:41:23,413 --> 00:41:25,160
- It's really good.
- Yes.

487
00:41:25,846 --> 00:41:28,996
But you have to return it
to the school library by tomorrow.

488
00:41:29,079 --> 00:41:30,426
- Tomorrow?
- Yes.

489
00:41:30,509 --> 00:41:32,411
Good luck. You can do it.

490
00:41:32,494 --> 00:41:34,283
Hey, Dad. It's me.

491
00:41:34,366 --> 00:41:37,222
I have to attend a conference.

492
00:41:38,364 --> 00:41:41,280
No, that was a club trip.
This is a conference.

493
00:41:43,774 --> 00:41:45,691
My allowance isn't enough
to pay the membership fee.

494
00:41:45,774 --> 00:41:46,933
EDITORIAL REPORTER - LEE YU-MI

495
00:41:47,016 --> 00:41:49,609
Yes, we get together to present.

496
00:41:49,692 --> 00:41:51,040
By tomorrow, okay?

497
00:41:52,117 --> 00:41:53,391
Thank you, Dad.

498
00:42:00,261 --> 00:42:03,619
Comprehensive class for repeaters.
My name is Lee Yu-mi. It's for this month.

499
00:42:04,857 --> 00:42:08,892
Comprehensive class for repeaters?
Lee Yu-mi.

500
00:42:10,820 --> 00:42:12,214
Your attendance...

501
00:42:14,616 --> 00:42:18,429
If you keep missing classes like this,
you could get expelled.

502
00:42:18,512 --> 00:42:20,328
There's only a month left
before the exams.

503
00:42:21,843 --> 00:42:23,751
I'm sorry. I won't miss any from now.

504
00:42:28,602 --> 00:42:30,410
Time's up.

505
00:42:30,493 --> 00:42:33,366
Raise both hands above your heads.

506
00:42:36,161 --> 00:42:38,732
Stop marking and raise your hands.

507
00:42:42,200 --> 00:42:44,572
The last person in each row
will collect the answer sheets.

508
00:42:51,192 --> 00:42:53,628
Those in the front row
can collect the questions.

509
00:43:03,030 --> 00:43:06,312
It will be hard to get admitted
with your score.

510
00:43:07,126 --> 00:43:10,580
I'm not sure.

511
00:43:10,663 --> 00:43:13,056
Are you interested in any other schools?

512
00:43:21,302 --> 00:43:22,700
Hello?

513
00:43:22,783 --> 00:43:24,913
Yu-mi. Where have you been?

514
00:43:24,996 --> 00:43:26,152
Did something happen?

515
00:43:28,822 --> 00:43:29,913
No.

516
00:43:30,753 --> 00:43:33,811
I've been busy.

517
00:43:34,803 --> 00:43:35,958
I see.

518
00:43:36,483 --> 00:43:38,341
Are you coming
to the general assembly tomorrow?

519
00:43:40,114 --> 00:43:41,319
The general assembly?

520
00:43:41,402 --> 00:43:43,509
The assembly for
editorial departments in Seoul.

521
00:43:45,299 --> 00:43:46,308
I see.

522
00:43:47,106 --> 00:43:48,885
I mentioned it last time.

523
00:43:50,123 --> 00:43:52,273
Right... I forgot.

524
00:43:52,930 --> 00:43:55,154
What is it? Can't you come?

525
00:43:55,848 --> 00:43:57,681
I can. I'll be there.

526
00:43:58,981 --> 00:44:00,211
What time is it?

527
00:44:00,900 --> 00:44:01,881
All right.

528
00:44:01,964 --> 00:44:03,881
Hello. Long time no see.

529
00:44:03,964 --> 00:44:07,483
I'm Han Ji-won
from Ehyeon Womans University.

530
00:44:07,566 --> 00:44:09,845
Hello, I'm Han Yu-young.

531
00:44:09,928 --> 00:44:12,114
Hello, I'm Kim Min-ji.

532
00:44:15,167 --> 00:44:17,207
Hello, I'm Lee Yu-mi.

533
00:44:17,290 --> 00:44:18,570
You're beautiful!

534
00:44:21,464 --> 00:44:23,500
As I suspected,
our new recruit is very popular.

535
00:44:23,583 --> 00:44:24,685
I'm so proud.

536
00:44:24,768 --> 00:44:25,961
She's pretty.

537
00:44:27,088 --> 00:44:29,971
Thank you. Our university
admits people based on looks.

538
00:44:31,749 --> 00:44:37,371
At last year's assembly,
we said we'd talk about this year's...

539
00:44:42,553 --> 00:44:43,610
Watch carefully.

540
00:44:44,386 --> 00:44:47,077
One, two, three.

541
00:44:48,275 --> 00:44:49,398
It disappeared.

542
00:44:50,251 --> 00:44:51,550
Here it is!

543
00:44:51,633 --> 00:44:52,707
Amazing.

544
00:44:53,703 --> 00:44:57,162
- What happened?
- Gosh, a doll is talking.

545
00:45:01,967 --> 00:45:04,128
GENERAL ASSEMBLY
OF UNIVERSITY EDITORIALS IN SEOUL

546
00:45:14,701 --> 00:45:16,259
Why are you outside?

547
00:45:20,263 --> 00:45:21,648
The heater

548
00:45:23,224 --> 00:45:24,550
gave me a headache.

549
00:45:29,304 --> 00:45:30,619
Do you want to go for a walk?

550
00:45:31,784 --> 00:45:33,745
This way will take us
to our school's back gate.

551
00:45:50,570 --> 00:45:54,109
Aren't you cold?
You don't have a jacket on.

552
00:45:55,674 --> 00:45:56,695
I'm okay.

553
00:46:03,188 --> 00:46:04,555
It's snowing.

554
00:46:04,638 --> 00:46:06,023
You're right.

555
00:46:13,781 --> 00:46:15,753
It's a bit chilly.

556
00:46:52,044 --> 00:46:53,208
Hello?

557
00:46:53,996 --> 00:46:56,119
Yu-mi? Is this Yu-mi?

558
00:46:58,245 --> 00:47:00,432
Yes, Ma'am. It's Yu-mi.

559
00:47:01,838 --> 00:47:03,515
Hey, what are you doing?

560
00:47:03,598 --> 00:47:05,995
You better come to school
to pick up your report card.

561
00:47:06,078 --> 00:47:07,861
It was announced ages ago.

562
00:47:12,021 --> 00:47:14,648
What did I get?

563
00:47:15,892 --> 00:47:19,469
Your score is worse than last year.

564
00:47:19,552 --> 00:47:23,125
Yu-mi. Must you go
to Ehyeon Womans University?

565
00:47:23,208 --> 00:47:25,588
Can't we lower the goal
and go to a different one in Seoul?

566
00:47:27,593 --> 00:47:29,921
Don't repeat a third time.
It'll be too hard on you.

567
00:47:30,004 --> 00:47:32,067
Keeping your pride
isn't that important.

568
00:47:34,544 --> 00:47:38,401
I'll call you back later. Okay.

569
00:48:01,630 --> 00:48:02,522
Do you want help?

570
00:48:02,605 --> 00:48:05,516
Yes. Can you help me put it on?

571
00:48:05,599 --> 00:48:08,930
Do you think
I'll be able to carry this around?

572
00:48:09,702 --> 00:48:11,232
Where are you going?

573
00:48:11,315 --> 00:48:13,404
Backpacking in Europe.

574
00:48:13,487 --> 00:48:16,715
Wow. I almost fell backwards.

575
00:48:17,175 --> 00:48:18,621
You're traveling? What about school?

576
00:48:18,704 --> 00:48:20,901
My classes finished last week.

577
00:48:20,984 --> 00:48:24,011
I tutored part-time
for seven months for this.

578
00:48:24,895 --> 00:48:26,443
What are you doing during your break?

579
00:48:29,237 --> 00:48:32,456
By the way, it's my first time
going abroad, so I'm scared.

580
00:48:33,485 --> 00:48:35,162
Shoot, I'm late.

581
00:48:35,245 --> 00:48:36,592
Bye, Yu-mi.

582
00:48:36,675 --> 00:48:38,382
Okay, bye.

583
00:49:31,905 --> 00:49:34,188
I don't like it when you
touch my stuff without asking.

584
00:49:36,729 --> 00:49:38,726
It was just sitting right there...

585
00:49:38,809 --> 00:49:40,364
Why do you have that anyway?

586
00:49:42,656 --> 00:49:43,684
For tutoring.

587
00:49:45,272 --> 00:49:47,053
I thought you didn't want a part-time job.

588
00:49:50,801 --> 00:49:52,844
I want to save up on my own
to go backpacking.

589
00:49:55,616 --> 00:49:56,916
Really?

590
00:50:03,019 --> 00:50:07,496
I'm going to New York next year.

591
00:50:07,579 --> 00:50:09,719
- New York?
- Yes.

592
00:50:09,802 --> 00:50:12,128
It's kind of like
an exchange student program.

593
00:50:12,211 --> 00:50:14,407
I'll spend my last year at that school.

594
00:50:18,355 --> 00:50:19,446
I see.

595
00:50:21,451 --> 00:50:22,423
Are you upset?

596
00:50:24,634 --> 00:50:26,477
No, it's good news for you.

597
00:50:28,139 --> 00:50:29,158
Congratulations.

598
00:50:35,212 --> 00:50:37,037
Don't go backpacking.

599
00:50:38,793 --> 00:50:40,088
Should we go together?

600
00:50:43,764 --> 00:50:44,859
Together?

601
00:50:44,942 --> 00:50:46,118
Yes.

602
00:50:46,201 --> 00:50:48,532
You can study English for a year,

603
00:50:48,615 --> 00:50:49,849
and I can go to school.

604
00:50:51,878 --> 00:50:55,414
Anyway, my mom suggested
we get married after graduation.

605
00:50:55,497 --> 00:50:57,356
She said we should go together.

606
00:50:58,959 --> 00:51:01,115
She wants to meet you.

607
00:51:03,468 --> 00:51:05,085
We'll end the class here.

608
00:51:06,208 --> 00:51:08,044
Thank you.

609
00:51:10,522 --> 00:51:12,338
Wait, guys.

610
00:51:13,414 --> 00:51:15,292
Raise your hand if you're a repeater.

611
00:51:18,160 --> 00:51:19,163
Hands down.

612
00:51:19,976 --> 00:51:21,303
Who's repeating a third time?

613
00:51:24,130 --> 00:51:25,737
Okay, down. Fourth time?

614
00:51:28,862 --> 00:51:31,612
Hey, don't laugh. How can you laugh?

615
00:51:32,667 --> 00:51:33,614
Guys.

616
00:51:33,697 --> 00:51:35,508
Yu-mi.

617
00:51:35,591 --> 00:51:39,403
Jae-ho is moving so far away to study,

618
00:51:39,486 --> 00:51:41,369
so I'm worried about sending him alone.

619
00:51:42,145 --> 00:51:44,801
Do you think your parents
will give you the permission?

620
00:51:45,368 --> 00:51:47,732
Right, what does your father do?

621
00:51:49,504 --> 00:51:51,937
Gosh, it's cold. It's so cold.

622
00:51:54,384 --> 00:51:55,742
Isn't it strange?

623
00:51:55,825 --> 00:51:59,033
The weather gets really cold
on the day of the entrance exam.

624
00:52:02,915 --> 00:52:05,329
Time flies, doesn't it?

625
00:52:05,412 --> 00:52:08,972
You sat there to have your meal
before taking yours.

626
00:52:10,845 --> 00:52:15,207
I'll go and spend a night in Hongcheon
before returning tomorrow.

627
00:52:15,781 --> 00:52:17,186
Really?

628
00:52:17,269 --> 00:52:18,920
Your parents will be so happy to see you.

629
00:52:20,668 --> 00:52:23,305
Gosh, you shouldn't have bought anything.

630
00:52:27,238 --> 00:52:28,385
It's bitter.

631
00:52:28,988 --> 00:52:31,447
What's good for you is always bitter.

632
00:52:33,020 --> 00:52:35,348
Why didn't you call us beforehand?

633
00:52:35,431 --> 00:52:37,549
I could've picked you up
from the terminal.

634
00:52:39,352 --> 00:52:40,380
Right...

635
00:52:43,391 --> 00:52:47,010
Dad, I was selected
as a distinguished student.

636
00:52:47,093 --> 00:52:48,026
Really?

637
00:52:49,301 --> 00:52:51,273
Do you get a scholarship?

638
00:52:52,829 --> 00:52:54,640
No, it's not like that.

639
00:52:54,723 --> 00:52:56,648
It's better.
I can go on a language training.

640
00:52:57,835 --> 00:52:59,299
What is that?

641
00:53:00,075 --> 00:53:04,456
I can go to the States
and study English for a year.

642
00:53:04,539 --> 00:53:05,599
With a scholarship?

643
00:53:08,100 --> 00:53:09,830
No, not really.

644
00:53:10,739 --> 00:53:13,288
They only give me the opportunity.

645
00:53:17,172 --> 00:53:18,360
I see.

646
00:53:19,060 --> 00:53:21,909
Everyone goes abroad to learn languages
these days. It's a must.

647
00:53:29,549 --> 00:53:30,529
Dad.

648
00:53:32,247 --> 00:53:33,906
Please help me just this once.

649
00:53:35,733 --> 00:53:39,032
I really want to excel.

650
00:53:40,718 --> 00:53:43,066
I don't think there will be
another chance like this.

651
00:53:44,182 --> 00:53:45,881
I promise this will be the last time.

652
00:53:48,724 --> 00:53:50,036
Please, Dad.

653
00:53:53,698 --> 00:53:56,263
Kang Jae-ho and Lee Yu-mi.
Two people heading to New York, right?

654
00:53:56,346 --> 00:53:57,540
- Yes.
- Yes.

655
00:54:00,160 --> 00:54:02,037
We tried our best to be prepared,

656
00:54:02,120 --> 00:54:04,218
but there's just so much to check.

657
00:54:04,759 --> 00:54:06,593
Also, here.

658
00:54:06,676 --> 00:54:10,085
This has his herbal medicine.

659
00:54:10,168 --> 00:54:11,771
Please make sure he takes them.

660
00:54:11,854 --> 00:54:12,829
I will, Mother.

661
00:54:12,912 --> 00:54:15,037
I feel at ease

662
00:54:15,120 --> 00:54:17,201
now that you're going with him.

663
00:54:18,551 --> 00:54:21,118
Make sure to look carefully
when you're picking the place to stay.

664
00:54:21,201 --> 00:54:22,829
If you don't, you'll end up--

665
00:54:22,912 --> 00:54:25,179
Mom. That's enough.

666
00:54:27,161 --> 00:54:29,979
By the way, where's your father?

667
00:54:30,062 --> 00:54:32,084
Gosh, that old man...

668
00:54:33,761 --> 00:54:36,043
From Incheon to New York JFK Airport.

669
00:54:36,126 --> 00:54:38,000
The passengers are
Kang Jae-ho and Lee Yu-mi.

670
00:54:38,083 --> 00:54:41,266
Please go to gate 36 before boarding time.

671
00:54:42,281 --> 00:54:43,924
- Thank you.
- Sure.

672
00:54:48,768 --> 00:54:50,550
Mom's over the top, isn't she?

673
00:54:50,633 --> 00:54:52,948
I thought she'd come in
all the way here with us.

674
00:54:53,031 --> 00:54:54,894
She's just worried, that's all.

675
00:54:56,518 --> 00:54:58,769
Should I take a close look
at your passport picture?

676
00:54:58,852 --> 00:54:59,971
No, don't.

677
00:55:02,256 --> 00:55:04,332
We have some time left, so wait here.

678
00:55:04,415 --> 00:55:06,157
- I'll get us some coffee.
- Okay.

679
00:55:06,890 --> 00:55:09,975
Right. Call your father one more time.

680
00:55:10,058 --> 00:55:11,680
I'm worried.

681
00:55:11,763 --> 00:55:12,774
Okay, I will.

682
00:55:31,836 --> 00:55:32,846
Hey, Mom.

683
00:55:34,388 --> 00:55:37,407
Dad. I'll be back soon.

684
00:55:38,180 --> 00:55:39,369
What are you saying? Talk slowly.

685
00:55:39,452 --> 00:55:43,479
Yu-mi is a fake. She's fake!

686
00:55:45,340 --> 00:55:49,826
Your father asked the TAs
and checked the whole school.

687
00:55:49,909 --> 00:55:53,066
They don't have a student
named Lee Yu-mi.

688
00:55:53,149 --> 00:55:54,076
What?

689
00:55:55,040 --> 00:55:56,612
Are you listening to me?

690
00:55:58,936 --> 00:56:03,293
They say there is no such student
at that school.

691
00:56:07,296 --> 00:56:09,814
Where on earth did you meet such a girl?

692
00:56:13,473 --> 00:56:15,626
You didn't board the plane yet, right?

693
00:56:15,709 --> 00:56:18,050
I came back to the airport.

694
00:56:21,686 --> 00:56:22,808
What about Mom?

695
00:56:25,550 --> 00:56:26,610
Okay.

